{"descriptions":[{"id":1357,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eWhen someone hasn\u0026rsquo;t heard what the speaker has said, or wishes to make him repeat it, he can use the particle \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཨས་\u003c/span\u003e, which raises a question about the preceding word. In a similar situation English would use interrogative pronouns.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསྦྲ་གུར་ནང་ལ་ཨས།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;In the tent?\u0026rdquo; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཡིན་དགོས་བྱུང་།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Sure!\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཞལ་པར་སླེབས་སོང་།\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཕེབས་རོགས་གནང་།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;There\u0026rsquo;s a phone call, come!\u0026rdquo; \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསུ།\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eང་ཨས། \u003c/span\u003e\u0026ldquo;Who? Me?\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:43 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:43 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}